<subSubSection pageId="29" pageNumber="30" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="29.[94,719,858,1139]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
The general appearance of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Santos-Silva &amp; Botero &amp; Wappes" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Erichson" baseAuthorityYear="1847" box="[457,718,858,883]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Aegomorphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="satellinus">
<emphasis box="[457,718,858,883]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Aegomorphus satellinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to that of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Germar, 1823)" authorityName="Santos-Silva &amp; Botero &amp; Wappes" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Germar" baseAuthorityYear="1823" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Aegomorphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jaspideus">
<emphasis box="[346,609,890,915]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Aegomorphus jaspideus</emphasis>
(Germar, 1823)
</taxonomicName>
making it difficult to separate them simply from the dorsal view. Fortunately, the mesoventral process (
<figureCitation box="[100,252,986,1011]" captionStart="Figures 121-129" captionStartId="24.[170,238,2042,2067]" captionTargetBox="[171,1493,368,2012]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[170,1493,368,2012]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="Figures 121-129. (121‑125) Aegomorphus consentaneus, male from Bolivia.(121) Dorsal habitus.(122)Ventral habitus.(123) Lateral habitus.(124) Head,frontal view. (125) Lower eye lobe. (126‑127) Aegomorphus satellinus, mesoventral process, male from Bolivia. (128‑129) Aegomorphus jaspideus, mesoventral process, male from Bolivia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3727909" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3727909/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Figs. 126-127</figureCitation>
) differs in the two species with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Santos-Silva &amp; Botero &amp; Wappes" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Erichson" baseAuthorityYear="1847" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Aegomorphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="satellinus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">A. satellinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
having a somewhat centrally flattened process with a small tubercle on each side of anterior margin. In 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Santos-Silva &amp; Botero &amp; Wappes" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Germar" baseAuthorityYear="1823" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Aegomorphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jaspideus">A. jaspideus</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
the mesoventral process (
<figureCitation box="[439,587,1082,1107]" captionStart="Figures 121-129" captionStartId="24.[170,238,2042,2067]" captionTargetBox="[171,1493,368,2012]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[170,1493,368,2012]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="Figures 121-129. (121‑125) Aegomorphus consentaneus, male from Bolivia.(121) Dorsal habitus.(122)Ventral habitus.(123) Lateral habitus.(124) Head,frontal view. (125) Lower eye lobe. (126‑127) Aegomorphus satellinus, mesoventral process, male from Bolivia. (128‑129) Aegomorphus jaspideus, mesoventral process, male from Bolivia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3727909" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3727909/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Figs. 128-129</figureCitation>
) is centrally tumid and lacks the tubercles.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
